{
  "texts": [
    "For any 0 < R 1 < R 2 -1 we define the annular region A R 1,R 2 to consist of all faces, edges, and vertices contained in the closure of B R 2 \\ B R 1.",
    "For any edge e ∈ E we moreover define For any n ≥ n 1, take R ′ > R large enough so that the support of C [1, n] is contained in B R ′ (recall that supp O ⊂ B R).",
    "Then the region A (en) R,R ′ has associated surface homeomorphic to a thrice punctured sphere.",
    "(two connected boundary components from the original annulus and one from the puncture at e n.) Moreover, denoting by S R ′ the outer boundary component of Σ A R,R ′, we have that ω n (t S R ′ (a)) = ψ n (t S R ′ (a)) = ω 1 (t S R ′ (a)) for any a ∈ Tube S R ′.",
    "Since ω 1 (t S R ′ (P 1)) = 1, it follows that the restrictions of ω n and ψ n to A (en) R,R ′ are given by density matrices in DA (en) R,R ′ (P 1, id, p X) = D A (en) R,R ′ (P 1, P X, p X),where the equality follows from Lemma 4.7."
  ]
